title: End Ever - Tales Of The Spooky Thunderfish - (2014)
description:
1410738413_CwwNMFjl.jpg 	27.72 KB
Description
END ever is ready to hit the stage with new material from their upcoming studio album Tales of the Spooky Thunderfish due to be released summer 2014. The band traveled to Big Fish Studios in San Diego CA, and spent time with Matt Van Allen for their latest release. END ever has made fans at every stop in their years of touring and shows, and plans to hit the road hard in the summer of 2014 to support their new album. Bringing with them the enthusiasm and talent that will captivate every concert goer along the way.
The unadulterated metal onslaught that is END ever, began in Billings, MT in 1998. END ever appeared at the 2001 Milwaukee Metal Fest and has shared the stage with such bands as Pop Evil, Adelitas Way, Seether, Floater, Exodus, Death Angle, Sepultura, Static-X, Diecast, Dope, Primer 55, Skinlab, Society One, Cattle Decapitation, Bloodlet, I.R.A.T.E, High On Fire, Drunkhorse, and Hemlock. The 10 time (2002-2013) winner of the Billings Outpost Tuney Award for Best Metal Act.

Members:

Mike Walters (vocals)
Matt Devitt (drums)
Mario Castillo (guitar)
Dave Kosmann Jr. (guitar, vocals)
Andre' Brown (bass, vocals)
